A fragment of copper alloy sword of Late Bronze Age period (c.1000&nbsp;- 800BC)

Description: The fragment is broadly rectangular in plan&nbsp;and lenticular&nbsp;in cross-section. The sides taper slightly in width. Either side of a raised centre is bevelled. The edges are worn.&nbsp;The object has worn breaks at each end. The sword has a dark brown patina wearing away to reveal a grey-green colour underneath.&nbsp;

Measurements:&nbsp;Length:&nbsp;26.3&nbsp;mm; Width:&nbsp;35.7&nbsp;mm; Thickness:&nbsp;8&nbsp;mm; Weight:&nbsp;33.12&nbsp;g
